"{\"uid\": \"foxnews.com-politics-election-integrity-group-dishes-out-50000-to-whistleblowers-6-figure-olympics-ad-buy-were-watching\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten, or redistributed.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 75, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a92025 FOX News Network, LLC.\", \"from\": 76, \"to\": 104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 82, \"end\": 98, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"FOX News Network\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 105, \"to\": 125, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Quotes displayed in real-time or delayed by at least 15 minutes.\", \"from\": 126, \"to\": 190, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Market data provided byFactset.\", \"from\": 191, \"to\": 222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Powered and implemented byFactSet Digital Solutions.Legal Statement.\", \"from\": 223, \"to\": 291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mutual Fund and ETF data provided byRefinitiv Lipper.\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 345, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 308, \"end\": 311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6406484666757017e-37, \"text\": \"ETF\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fox News national correspondent Bryan Llenas has more on the program committing to deploy more than 100,000 volunteers and aggressive attorneys on Special Report.\", \"from\": 347, \"to\": 509, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 347, \"end\": 355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.557632469587152e-17, \"text\": \"Fox News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}, {\"begin\": 379, \"end\": 391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryan_Llenas\", \"score\": 0.9999948482046339, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bryan Llenas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryan_Llenas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryan_Llenas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A newly formedelection watchdognonprofit organization has started paying out tens of thousands of dollars in \\\"bounties\\\" to election whistleblowers as part of its unique goal of promoting election integrity by encouraging whistleblowers to come forward.\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Fair Election Fund, arecently formednational election integrity watchdog group, is announcing this week it is awarding an initial $50,000 in \\\"bounties\\\" to whistleblowers who have reported first-hand knowledge of voter fraud or irregularities across four states, including North Carolina and Michigan.\", \"from\": 765, \"to\": 1069, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1041, \"end\": 1055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Carolina\", \"score\": 0.9999966846708436, \"rank\": 3.3067581384192515e-06, \"text\": \"North Carolina\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Carolina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Carolina\"}, {\"begin\": 1060, \"end\": 1068, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michigan\", \"score\": 0.9999987026821375, \"rank\": 1.188503140220143e-06, \"text\": \"Michigan\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michigan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michigan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Fair Election fund was set up earlier this year pledging millions of dollars to promote election integrity by paying and protecting whistleblowers on the front lines who are able to identify issues at polling places and election offices.\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1312, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The group says it has heard from numerous whistleblowers across the country reporting issues receiving multiple ballots, delayed ballots, mailing address errors, independent parties blocked from overseeing counting, receiving ballots without requesting one and other issues.\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1588, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"WISCONSIN SUPREME COURT NEW LIBERAL MAJORITY REVERSES RULING THAT BANNED MOST BALLOT DROP BOXES IN SWING STATE  A new election integrity group is paying whistleblowers who report voting irregularities.\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1791, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1590, \"end\": 1613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wisconsin_Supreme_Court\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"WISCONSIN SUPREME COURT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wisconsin_Supreme_Court\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wisconsin_Supreme_Court\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(PAUL J. RICHARDS/AFP via Getty Images)  \\\"The Fair Election Fund is thrilled that our incentives are working and we are learning more about systemic problems with our election system, but this is just the beginning,\\\" Doug Collins, former congressman from Georgia and Fair Election Fund Senior Advisor, said in the press release.\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 2119, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1817, \"end\": 1822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9999990677465374, \"rank\": 5.33363319678858e-07, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}, {\"begin\": 2008, \"end\": 2020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doug_Collins_(basketball)\", \"score\": 0.8171251233035431, \"rank\": 0.21730119524172167, \"text\": \"Doug Collins\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doug_Collins_(basketball)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doug_Collins_(basketball)\"}, {\"begin\": 2046, \"end\": 2053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Georgia\", \"score\": 0.9903073591364638, \"rank\": 0.007790887596394004, \"text\": \"Georgia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Georgia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Georgia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Fair Election Fund today is sharing the stories of the first brave whistleblowers who stepped up and exposed the wrongdoing they saw in the election process and we are grateful for their contribution.\", \"from\": 2121, \"to\": 2326, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We must shine a light on these abuses and root out election fraud before Americans head to the polls this November.\\\"\", \"from\": 2327, \"to\": 2443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ARIZONA ELECTION WORKER SEEN STEALING FROM SENATE SECURITY DESK DAY BEFORE ELECTION CENTER THEFT: OFFICIALS  The ads will run during the Summer Olympics in Paris.\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2601, \"end\": 2606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999985831537775, \"rank\": 1.416848417947458e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(AP Photo/Aurelien Morissard, File)  The group says in the press release that the \\\"success\\\" of the \\\"initial bounties\\\" shows the need for the group to expand, which it will do into key swing states in a six-figure digital ad buy during the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2607, \"to\": 2855, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thenew ad, titled \\\"We are Watching,\\\" will run in the swing states of Arizona, Nevada, Wisconsin, Michigan, Pennsylvania, Georgia and North Carolina and tells the story of a Connecticut Democratic operativerecently chargedin an absentee ballot stuffing investigation.\", \"from\": 2857, \"to\": 3123, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2926, \"end\": 2933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arizona\", \"score\": 0.9999999996953193, \"rank\": 2.6888726522381373e-10, \"text\": \"Arizona\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arizona\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arizona\"}, {\"begin\": 2935, \"end\": 2941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nevada\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.541870569452062e-16, \"text\": \"Nevada\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nevada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nevada\"}, {\"begin\": 2943, \"end\": 2952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wisconsin\", \"score\": 0.9999999998826752, \"rank\": 1.1444293782452538e-10, \"text\": \"Wisconsin\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wisconsin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wisconsin\"}, {\"begin\": 2954, \"end\": 2962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michigan\", \"score\": 0.9999987026821375, \"rank\": 1.188503140220143e-06, \"text\": \"Michigan\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michigan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michigan\"}, {\"begin\": 2964, \"end\": 2976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pennsylvania\", \"score\": 0.9999605143313208, \"rank\": 3.707893512332147e-05, \"text\": \"Pennsylvania\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pennsylvania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pennsylvania\"}, {\"begin\": 2978, \"end\": 2985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Georgia\", \"score\": 0.9903073591364638, \"rank\": 0.007790887596394004, \"text\": \"Georgia\", \"t